msgid "MongoDB 3.0 and SCRAM-SHA-1"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/3.0-scram.txt:10
# dcb5a8a8914945b488ed9424396170fe
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/3.0-scram.txt:12
# f77fea80e1ad4b899543e6e08a86629c
msgid "MongoDB 3.0 includes support for the :ref:`SCRAM-SHA-1 <authentication-scram-sha-1>` challenge-response user authentication mechanism. This changes how MongoDB uses and stores user credentials.  If your deployment uses authentication and authorization, you must upgrade the authentication schema in addition to upgrading MongoDB processes if you wish to make use of ``SCRAM-SHA-1``."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/3.0-scram.txt:19
# 5c85f58be5094e5e93552bfa3100ff2b
msgid "You may, alternatively, opt to continue to use the ``MONGODB-CR`` challenge-response mechanism and skip this upgrade. See the :ref:`SCRAM-SHA-1 <authentication-scram-sha-1>` documentation for further information on its advantages."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/3.0-scram.txt:25
# 27112f28728c4fbe88902aeb09460ef5
msgid "Recommendation"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/3.0-scram.txt:27
# 937a85e39f744350991b86782ce920ad
msgid "``SCRAM-SHA-1`` represents a significant improvement in security over ``MONGODB-CR``, the previous default authentication mechanism: you are strongly urged to upgrade. The next major version of MongoDB is likely to remove all support for ``MONGODB-CR``."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/3.0-scram.txt:33
# 8a2ae23ef08a497c9cd6afce9cb24954
msgid "Upgrade Scenarios"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/3.0-scram.txt:35
# 151310c735f347a9903278d2bddcb025
msgid "The following scenarios are possible when upgrading from 2.6 to 3.0:"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/3.0-scram.txt:37
# 2b7a2ecf14ae44079e31046c35d8a4bb
msgid "If you are starting with a new 3.0 installation without any users or upgrading from a 2.6 database that has no users and wish to use ``SCRAM-SHA-1``, **no action is required**. All new users created will have the correct format for ``SCRAM-SHA-1``."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/3.0-scram.txt:42
# 03d6fcd0f2324a06954eed542b3e116d
msgid "If you are upgrading from a 2.6 database with existing data, including users, and wish to continue to use ``MONGODB-CR``, **no action is required**. All new users created under 3.0 will continue to use the same authentication model as users already in the database. You can execute the upgrade to ``SCRAM-SHA-1`` at any point in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/3.0-scram.txt:48
# 8dc35e5aafda474f91d35f75c3ac852a
msgid "If you are upgrading from a 2.6 database with existing data, including users, and wish to upgrade to ``SCRAM-SHA-1``, you may follow the steps under the heading :ref:`Upgrade a 2.6 Database to Use SCRAM-SHA-1 on 3.0 <3.0-upgrade-mongodb-cr-to-scram>`."
msgstr ""

